-- Hong Kong Bishop Acknowledges Sex Scandals in Diocese, Morning Post Says
-- B y   D e b r a   M a o
-- 2010-10-18T00:29:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/hong-kong-bishop-acknowledges-sex-scandals-in-diocese-morning-post-says.html
Hong Kong’s most senior Catholic
leader acknowledged for the first time that there had been sex
scandals in the local diocese, the South China Morning Post
reported.  Bishop John Tong Hon, speaking in the city at a celebration
of World Mission yesterday, didn’t provide details on the
scandals or identify people involved, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Debra Mao in Hong Kong at 
